    "content": "<h1 id=\"technical-documentation\">Technical Documentation<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#technical-documentation\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h1>\n<p>This section covers how Chekameh was built — the architecture, tools, and decisions behind the project.</p>\n<h2 id=\"overview\">Overview<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#overview\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<p>Chekameh combines historical research with modern web technology. The goal was to make Persian poetry accessible through interactive visualization while maintaining academic rigor.</p>\n<h2 id=\"stack-tools\">Stack &amp; Tools<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#stack-tools\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"frontend\">Frontend<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#frontend\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Interactive map library</li>\n<li>Timeline visualization</li>\n<li>Responsive design for mobile and desktop</li>\n<li>Bilingual support (English and Persian)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"backend\">Backend<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#backend\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Data processing pipelines</li>\n<li>API for poet, city, and era information</li>\n<li>Search functionality</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"data\">Data<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#data\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Structured poet biographies</li>\n<li>Geographic coordinates for historical cities</li>\n<li>Timeline metadata</li>\n<li>Poem collections and references</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"ai-features\">AI Features<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#ai-features\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Chatbot for answering questions about poets and poems</li>\n<li>Contextual suggestions based on location and era</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"key-features\">Key Features<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#key-features\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"interactive-map\">Interactive Map<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#interactive-map\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h3>\n<p>The map shows literary centers across the Persian-speaking world. Toggle between eras to see how centers of poetry shifted over time. Click on cities to see which poets lived or worked there.</p>\n<h3 id=\"timeline\">Timeline<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#timeline\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h3>\n<p>Slide through centuries to see when each poet was active. The timeline syncs with the map — select a time period and the map updates to show relevant locations.</p>\n<h3 id=\"poet-profiles\">Poet Profiles<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#poet-profiles\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h3>\n<p>Each poet has a dedicated page with biographical info, major works, associated cities, and connections to other poets.</p>\n<h3 id=\"search\">Search<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#search\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h3>\n<p>Find poets by name, era, location, or keywords in their work.</p>\n<h3 id=\"chatbot\">Chatbot<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#chatbot\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h3>\n<p>Ask natural language questions about Persian poetry. The bot draws from the site's data to provide context-aware answers.</p>\n<h2 id=\"architecture\">Architecture<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#architecture\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<!-- Detailed architecture docs to be added -->\n\n<p>The system is designed to separate data from presentation. This makes it easier to update content without touching the codebase.</p>\n<h2 id=\"development-setup\">Development Setup<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#development-setup\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<!-- Installation and setup instructions to be added -->\n\n<h2 id=\"api-reference\">API Reference<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#api-reference\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<!-- API documentation to be added -->\n\n<h2 id=\"contributing-code\">Contributing Code<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#contributing-code\" title=\"Permanent link\">&para;</a></h2>\n<p>See the <a href=\"/en/resources/\">Resources section</a> for guidelines on contributing to the codebase.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><em>More technical details coming soon.</em></p>",
